#### Example 8.1 Determining the Roots of the Characteristic Equation for a Parallel RLC Circuit

a) Calculate the roots of the characteristic equation dictating the transient behavior of the voltage in Fig. 8.5 for $R=200 \Omega, L=50 \mathrm{mH}$, and $C=0.2 \mu \mathrm{~F}$.
b) Determine if the response is overdamped, underdamped, or critically damped.
c) Repeat (a) and (b) for $R=312.5 \Omega$.
d) Find the value of $R$ that results in a critically damped response.

Image description:
